==English==

===Etymology 1===
Early Modern English (ca. 1500) slang term meaning "beggar's child".  Possibly from {{der|en|sco|bratchet||bitch, hound}}.  Or, possibly originally a dialectal word, from northern and western England and the Midlands, for a "makeshift or ragged garment," from {{der|en|ang|bratt||cloak}}, which is from a {{der|en|cel|-}} source ({{der|en|sga|-}} {{m|ga|brat||cloak, cloth}}).

